05/27/86 list_scope, ls

Syntax: ls {-control_arg}


Syntax as an active request: [ls {-control_arg}]


Function: lists the current scope settings.  As an active request
returns the current scope settings.


Control arguments:
-table name_1 {...nameN}, -tb name1 {...nameN}
   lists scope information for the specified tables only.


Notes:
If -table is not specified, scope information for every permanent
table is listed.
